Name: Kakamega Rainforest
Description: Kakamega Rainforest is a national reserve in Western Kenya. It is part of a larger area that makes up the last primeval rainforest in the country, and home to various monkeys and hundreds of bird species, some of which are threatened.

Name: Aberdare National Park
Description: Aberdare National Park is a 767-km² national park in the central highlands west of Mount Kenya, 180 km from Nairobi

Name: Sibiloi National Park
Description: Sibiloi National Park is on the north-eastern shore of Lake Turkana in the Northern Rift Valley of Kenya. It is part of the Lake Turkana National Parks UNESCO World Heritage site, recognised in 1997.

Name: Mount Elgon National Park
Description: Mount Elgon National Park is a park straddling the border of Uganda and Kenya.

Name: Lake Nakuru National Park
Description: Lake Nakuru National Park is one of Kenya’s two Premium Parks, and is a birdlover’s paradise. It surrounds Lake Nakuru in the Central Rift Conservation Area in the Southern Rift Valley region of Kenya. Originally protected as a bird sanctuary, this park hosts over 400 bird species, including 5 globally threatened species, and is an important stop on the African-Eurasian Migratory Flyway. This park was also the first national Rhino sanctuary and hosts one of the world’s highest concentrations of the Black Rhinoceros.

Name: Mount Kenya
Description: Mount Kenya is located near the center of Kenya about 150 km north of Nairobi. At 5300 m (17,000 feet) it is Africa's second highest mountain, after Kilimanjaro.

Name: Maasai Mara National Park
Description: Maasai Mara National Reserve is in the southwest of Kenya. The Maasai Mara is not a National Park, but rather a National Reserve belonging to the Maasai people and administered by the local county councils. It is one of the best known and most popular reserves in Africa.

Name: Nairobi National Park
Description: Nairobi National Park is the closest national park to Nairobi in Kenya.  It is a half-hour drive from the city, making it a good destination for a day trip.

Name: Tsavo East National Park
Description: Tsavo is in Kenya close to the city of Mombasa.

Name: Tsavo West National Park
Description: Tsavo West is in Kenya close to the city of Mombasa.

Name: Amboseli National Park
Description: Amboseli National Park is in Kenya.
